{
  "doc_id": "53878",
  "text": "Laboratory simulation-based skills training and assessment for MAS surgical skills include lower fidelity physical box/video trainers and higher fidelity virtual reality trainers. The physical box trainers use actual laparoscopic instruments and an optical system that allows the trainee to perform tasks under videoscopic guidance [CITATION_1] . Virtual reality trainers use computergenerated instruments to perform computer-generated tasks. There is a spectrum of machines available now with many of them incorporating haptic feedback.",
  "correct_citation": {
